title: Police sweep Kuala Lumpur airport after Kim Jong-nam death
text: Police sweep Kuala Lumpur airport for toxic chemicals as two 'assassins' arrested over the nerve gas killing of Kim Jong-nam say they were 'good time girls hired for Â£72' Two women assassinated Kim Jong Nam in Kuala Lumpur airport on February 13 Police have been sweeping the airport in a bid to locate toxic chemicals After a full search early on Sunday morning the airport was later declared safe Malaysian police say Kim Jong Un's half brother had nerve agent on his face VX Suspected attackers, Indonesian woman and Vietnamese woman, in custody They are understood to have admitted they had worked in massage parlours Alleged assassin Siti Aishah said she was paid to put 'baby oil' in victim's face
